oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Caruthers Hall at Cumberland University
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Black and white photograph of Caruthers Hall at Cumberland University.
Built in 1878 by Robert L. Caruthers, Caruthers Hall is home of the Cumberland University Law School. It was named for Abram Caruthers, the University's first Professor of Law (brother to Robert).
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
